<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="270" pageId="30" pageNumber="269" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,1875,2007]" lastBlockId="31.[151,1436,1522,1580]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="270" pageId="30" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1875,1900]" pageId="30" pageNumber="269">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[282,501,1875,1900]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Vaughanites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="269" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="leptus">
<emphasis box="[282,501,1875,1900]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="269">Vaughanites leptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the Miocene of 
<collectingCountry box="[966,1059,1875,1900]" name="Jamaica" pageId="30" pageNumber="269">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
, and classified in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1340,1436,1875,1900]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="269" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Turridae</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[151,286,1910,1935]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="269" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Borsoniinae">Borsoniinae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Woodring" box="[334,534,1910,1935]" pageId="30" pageNumber="269" refString="Woodring, W. P. (1928) Miocene mollusks from Bowden, Jamaica. Part II. Gastropoda and discussion of the results. Contributions to the Geology and Palaeontology of the West Indies. Carnegie Institution of Washington, Publication No. 385, 1 - 564." type="book chapter" year="1928">
Woodring (
<number box="[464,525,1911,1935]" pageId="30" pageNumber="269" value="1928.0">1928</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It is characterized by a particularly long canal and the two strong columellar folds, better seen when the shell is slightly turned counter-clockwise, similar to the plaits of 
<taxonomicName box="[1276,1376,1947,1972]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mitridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="269" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Mitridae</taxonomicName>
. The protoconch is unknown, all nine specimens cited by Woodring have a broken apex. 
<taxonomicName box="[1087,1298,1982,2007]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Vaughanites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="269" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="leptus">
<emphasis box="[1087,1298,1982,2007]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="269">Vaughanites leptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only record of 
<taxonomicName box="[264,438,1522,1547]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramimitridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="31" pageNumber="270" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Pyramimitridae</taxonomicName>
in the Atlantic Ocean after the late Oligocene apparent disappearance of the family in Europe.
</paragraph>
